{"lemma":"مَعْبَدِ","slug":"مَعْبَدِ","root":"ع.ب.د","root_slug":"ع-ب-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27816","n27817","n27819"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place of worship, temple"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the root ع ب د (ʕ b d)."},"ipa":["/maʕ.bad/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27816","headword_ar":"مَعْبَدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdapN","text_ar":"عِبَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaEab~adN","text_ar":"مُتَعَبَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27817","headword_ar":"مِعْبَدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shovel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spade, of iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHaApN","text_ar":"مِسْحَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAbidu","text_ar":"مَعَابِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n27819","headword_ar":"مُعَبَّدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rendered submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable; broken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trained;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*al~alN","text_ar":"مُذَلَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anointed with tar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rendered submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose whole skin is anointed with tar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mangy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scabby, whose fur has fallen off by degrees, and which is set apart from the other camels to be anointed with tar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered submissive by the mange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected with the mange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with incurable mange"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L. [And, applied to a camel, it has other meanings, which see in what follows.]) [And hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiynapN muEab~adapN","text_ar":"سَفِينَةٌ مُعَبَّدَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat, tarred:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, O, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smeared with fat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, L.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a road,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beaten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*al~alN","text_ar":"مُذَلَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trodden;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelled by many passengers going to and fro:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*al~alN","text_ar":"مُذَلَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to other things also. (K.) ―         -b3-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wooden pin, peg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stake."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, O, K, TA. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuw^at~adu","text_ar":"المُوَتَّدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwatidu","text_ar":"الوَتِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) So in the following verse of Ibn-Mukbil:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waDam~anotu A^arosaAna AljiyaAdi muEab~adFA\n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*aA maA DarabonaA raA^osahu laA yuran~aHu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I made a wooden peg to be a guarantee for the ropes of the coursers: when we beat its head, it did not wabble"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, O, TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Honoured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treated with honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and served;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a camel. (L.) Thus it has two contr. significations. (K.) ―         -b5-  And A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left unridden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L.) ―         -b6-  And, applied to a stallion [camel],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excited by lust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by vehement lust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b7-  Also, applied to a country, or tract of land,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In which is no footprint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"track, nor any sign of the way, nor water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baladN muEab~adN","text_ar":"بَلَدٌ مُعَبَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.)"}],"source_refs":["A","L","S","O","K","Sh","AO","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}